00:12:49.150 --> 00:12:51.760
nobody really cares about
spreadsheets, especially

00:12:51.760 --> 00:12:52.960
myself.

00:12:52.960 --> 00:12:56.680
Calculator, because it helps
us predict what we can do.

00:12:56.680 --> 00:12:59.950
So actually while
bringing in the equation

00:12:59.950 --> 00:13:01.670
from the previous
one-- can we go back?

00:13:01.670 --> 00:13:02.450
That one.

00:13:02.450 --> 00:13:04.241
So once we had this
equation, and we put it

00:13:04.241 --> 00:13:06.310
into the spreadsheet,
we suddenly

00:13:06.310 --> 00:13:08.720
started questioning where
the value was as well.

00:13:08.720 --> 00:13:10.178
So there was a lot
of things we put

00:13:10.178 --> 00:13:14.030
into the original model that
suddenly just made no sense.

00:13:14.030 --> 00:13:16.390
So it really gave
us a good lesson

00:13:16.390 --> 00:13:19.390
on what we should
be tracking and why,

00:13:19.390 --> 00:13:20.510
so it was really useful.

00:13:23.330 --> 00:13:27.180
And then the next part is what
the model actually gave us.

00:13:27.180 --> 00:13:31.670
So the first thing is, it
gave us clarity about what--

00:13:31.670 --> 00:13:34.070
across all departments,
about what it is we're doing.

00:13:34.070 --> 00:13:37.469
So the CEO, Nick,
no longer had to ask

00:13:37.469 --> 00:13:39.260
about where the
[INAUDIBLE] was coming from

00:13:39.260 --> 00:13:41.060
and how we could increase it.

00:13:41.060 --> 00:13:43.320
Clear as day in this model.

00:13:43.320 --> 00:13:45.710
And then products didn't
have to necessarily ask

00:13:45.710 --> 00:13:46.920
