00:14:03.330 --> 00:14:07.190
and "Show me the
money," but that's--

00:14:07.190 --> 00:14:09.080
it's not too bad.

00:14:09.080 --> 00:14:10.550
And then the resources--

00:14:10.550 --> 00:14:13.390
the big thing we realized is
that, because we're a receipt

00:14:13.390 --> 00:14:15.800
app, and we do a
lot with finances,

00:14:15.800 --> 00:14:19.599
we should be putting a lot
of priority into accountants.

00:14:19.599 --> 00:14:21.140
And that's something
we've not really

00:14:21.140 --> 00:14:23.750
done too much of in the past,
so it was a huge wake up call.

00:14:23.750 --> 00:14:26.600
That was a huge lever there,
that if we put more effort

00:14:26.600 --> 00:14:29.180
into that, we could
essentially get

00:14:29.180 --> 00:14:33.020
lots more users a lot easier
and help them keep retained.

00:14:33.020 --> 00:14:35.420
Now, that also
helped with hires.

00:14:35.420 --> 00:14:39.170
So one of the problems you
have, that we certainly have,

00:14:39.170 --> 00:14:41.240
is going trigger
happy on glass door

00:14:41.240 --> 00:14:44.275
and just hiring the wrong
people at the wrong time.

00:14:44.275 --> 00:14:45.650
